00:33:19.940 --> 00:33:21.230
It's not going anywhere.

00:33:21.230 --> 00:33:22.730
Or you can think
about it in the way

00:33:22.730 --> 00:33:24.397
that the energy is
going back and forth.

00:33:42.273 --> 00:33:43.440
I did not realize, actually.

00:33:43.440 --> 00:33:46.965
I did not the phasors
last time, did I?

00:33:46.965 --> 00:33:47.465
Did I?

00:33:47.465 --> 00:33:48.455
I guess I didn't.

00:33:58.490 --> 00:34:00.460
So I guess I pulled a fast one.

00:34:00.460 --> 00:34:03.250
A few minutes ago, I was
talking about the difficulty

00:34:03.250 --> 00:34:04.710
of trigonometry.

00:34:04.710 --> 00:34:07.240
And I said that's why I
introduced phasors last time.

00:34:07.240 --> 00:34:08.230
I was mistaken.

00:34:08.230 --> 00:34:10.929
I had not introduced
