membrane with the sound wave

00:52:02.330 --> 00:52:03.910
propagating on it.

00:52:03.910 --> 00:52:06.240
And now the reason that
particles are connected,

00:52:06.240 --> 00:52:08.550
that they execute a
coordinated motion

00:52:08.550 --> 00:52:10.950
is because of the
interatomic forces

00:52:10.950 --> 00:52:13.320
between the membrane particles.

00:52:13.320 --> 00:52:15.180
If it is an
electromagnetic wave,

00:52:15.180 --> 00:52:19.050
then it is a field
that is distributed.

00:52:19.050 --> 00:52:21.210
And, of course, it
knows to be connected

00:52:21.210 --> 00:52:23.060
because of Maxim's equations.

00:52:23.060 --> 00:52:25.350
There's things like charge
conservation and so on that

00:52:25.350 --> 00:52:27.880
force it to act this way.

00:52:27.880 --> 00:52:29.790
So a wave is actually
a distributed system,

00:52:29.790 --> 00:52:37.230
where the physics force
an extended systems--

00:52:37.230 --> 00:52:40.470
particles, or fields, or
whatever the case may be--

00:52:40.470 --> 00:52:42.878
to execute a coordinated motion.

00:52:42.878 --> 00:52:45.420
That's the difference between
that simple harmonic oscillator

00:52:45.420 --> 00:52:46.795
where you just
have one particle.

00:52:46.795 --> 00:52:48.378
Now, you can go from
